==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elysium
<hw>E*ly"sium</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*l⟦icr⟧zh"⟦ucr⟧m <i>or</i>
⟦esl⟧*l⟦icr⟧zh"⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Elysiums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Elysia</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>'Hly`sion</grk>,
<grk>'Hly`sion pedi`on</grk>, Elysian field.]</ety> <fld>(Anc.
Myth.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A dwelling place assigned to happy souls
after death; the seat of future happiness; Paradise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, any delightful place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>Elysium</qex> more pure and bright than that of the
Greeks.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elytriform</ent>⟦br⟧
